 
<p>
New Zealand thinks it can
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/apr/27/new-zealand-too-reliant-on-tree-planting-to-meet-net-zero-emissions-targets-experts-warn">plant enough trees</a>
to outweigh all its greenhouse gas emissions.
<p>
<a href="/archives/2021-sep-dec.html#5_November_2021_(Trees_alone_are_not_the_answer)">That is very risky</a>.
What if the trees die?  That has <a href="/archives/2020-jan-apr.html#5_February_2020_(A_short_Forestation_Day)">happened before</a>
in big tree-planting projects.
  It is also no example for the rest of the world to follow.








